<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 1:59AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow will impact portions of north-central
Montana through 300 AM MST...
At 156 AM MST, Doppler radar was tracking A moderate to heavy band
of snow over Cascade and Choteau counties.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph. Snow, with visibility below one
half mile at times.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Snowfall, with visibility below one half mile and slippery
roads.
Locations impacted include...
Great Falls, Fort Benton, Cascade, Stanford, Belt, Geraldine, Fort
Shaw, Highwood, Black Eagle, Geyser, Fort Shaw, Carter, Neihart,
Floweree, Windham, Eden, Stockett, First Peoples Buffalo Jump State
Park, Shonkin and Loma.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Use caution if traveling.</instruction>
